<bibRefCitation author="Basilewsky, P." box="[192,509,1186,1210]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 472" refId="ref7374" refString="Basilewsky, P. 1977. Revision du genre Graphipterus Latreille (Coleoptera Carabidae). Musee Royal de l'Afrique Centrale, Annales, Serie in- 8 o, Sciences Zoologiques 221: 1 - 472." type="journal article" year="1977">Basilewsky (1977: 82–88)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[192,1440,1249,1882]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,441,1249,1274]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Taxonomic Notes.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Burgeon, L." box="[449,640,1250,1274]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" pagination="273 - 351" refId="ref7492" refString="Burgeon, L. 1929. Monographie du genre Graphipterus Latr. Annales de la Societe Entomologique du Belgique 69: 273 - 351." type="journal article" year="1929">Burgeon (1929)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Basilewsky, P." box="[704,930,1250,1274]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 472" refId="ref7374" refString="Basilewsky, P. 1977. Revision du genre Graphipterus Latreille (Coleoptera Carabidae). Musee Royal de l'Afrique Centrale, Annales, Serie in- 8 o, Sciences Zoologiques 221: 1 - 472." type="journal article" year="1977">Basilewsky (1977)</bibRefCitation>
placed this species in synonymy with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Dejean" baseAuthorityYear="1831" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Graphipterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cordiger">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">G. cordiger</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Basilewsky, P." box="[354,578,1282,1306]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 472" refId="ref7374" refString="Basilewsky, P. 1977. Revision du genre Graphipterus Latreille (Coleoptera Carabidae). Musee Royal de l'Afrique Centrale, Annales, Serie in- 8 o, Sciences Zoologiques 221: 1 - 472." type="journal article" year="1977">Basilewsky (1977)</bibRefCitation>
recognized a total of nine subspecific taxa under that single polytypic species. Application of the polytypic species concept to this group of taxa is not straightforward, as shown by the fact that Basilewsky could only offer a partial key to subspecies (
<bibRefCitation author="Basilewsky, P." box="[1139,1390,1346,1370]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 472" refId="ref7374" refString="Basilewsky, P. 1977. Revision du genre Graphipterus Latreille (Coleoptera Carabidae). Musee Royal de l'Afrique Centrale, Annales, Serie in- 8 o, Sciences Zoologiques 221: 1 - 472." type="journal article" year="1977">Basilewsky 1977: 78</bibRefCitation>
, 80) and a map (
<bibRefCitation author="Basilewsky, P." box="[335,545,1378,1402]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 472" refId="ref7374" refString="Basilewsky, P. 1977. Revision du genre Graphipterus Latreille (Coleoptera Carabidae). Musee Royal de l'Afrique Centrale, Annales, Serie in- 8 o, Sciences Zoologiques 221: 1 - 472." type="journal article" year="1977">Basilewsky 1977</bibRefCitation>
: Carte 9) which shows clear areas of overlap between many of the alleged subspecific forms (e.g. between 
<emphasis box="[577,765,1410,1434]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">G. c. betshuana</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[826,1039,1410,1434]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">G. c. subhamatus</emphasis>
, between 
<emphasis box="[1162,1351,1410,1434]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">G. c. betshuana</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">
G. c. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peringuey" authorityYear="1892" box="[219,378,1442,1466]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Graphipterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zambezianus">zambezianus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, and between 
<emphasis box="[555,725,1442,1466]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">
G. c. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1848" box="[617,725,1442,1466]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Graphipterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hamatus">hamatus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[787,981,1442,1466]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">
G. c. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peringuey" authorityYear="1896" box="[849,981,1442,1466]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Graphipterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="transfugus">transfugus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
). Furthermore, several pairs of putative subspecies have identical patterns of elytral pubescence and can be separated only by collecting locality (e.g. 
<emphasis box="[348,510,1506,1530]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">
G. c. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Dejean" baseAuthorityYear="1831" box="[410,510,1506,1530]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Graphipterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cordiger">cordiger</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[571,776,1506,1530]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">G. c. subcordiger</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[791,961,1506,1530]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">
G. c. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1848" box="[853,961,1506,1530]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Graphipterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hamatus">hamatus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[1023,1236,1506,1530]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">G. c. subhamatus</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[1251,1440,1506,1530]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">G. c. betshuana</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[245,435,1538,1562]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">
<taxonomicName box="[245,427,1538,1562]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Graphipterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="cordiger" subSpecies="wahlbergi">G. c. wahlbergi</taxonomicName>
;
</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Basilewsky, P." box="[441,650,1538,1562]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 472" refId="ref7374" refString="Basilewsky, P. 1977. Revision du genre Graphipterus Latreille (Coleoptera Carabidae). Musee Royal de l'Afrique Centrale, Annales, Serie in- 8 o, Sciences Zoologiques 221: 1 - 472." type="journal article" year="1977">Basilewsky 1977</bibRefCitation>
). As discussed above under 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Dejean" baseAuthorityYear="1831" box="[986,1121,1538,1562]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Graphipterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cordiger">
<emphasis box="[986,1121,1538,1562]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">G. cordiger</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, many of these difficulties can be resolved by dividing this single polytypic taxon into two distinct species, one with a rounded, lobe-shaped median patch of pubescence on the elytra, the other with a transverse, rectangular median patch of pubescence on the elytra. The observed areas of overlap between the subspecies always involve a form with a lobe-shaped pubescence patch on the elytra (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">
G. c. subhamatus, G. c. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peringuey" authorityYear="1892" box="[1211,1373,1666,1690]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Graphipterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zambezianus">zambezianus</taxonomicName>
, G. c. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1848" box="[192,300,1698,1722]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Graphipterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hamatus">hamatus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
) and a form with a transverse pubescence patch on the elytra (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">
G. c. betshuana, G. c. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peringuey" authorityYear="1896" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Graphipterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="transfugus">transfugus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
). The forms with identical patterns of pubescence can be interpreted as disjunct forms of either 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Dejean" baseAuthorityYear="1831" box="[192,328,1762,1786]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Graphipterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cordiger">
<emphasis box="[192,328,1762,1786]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">G. cordiger</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(in the case of 
<emphasis box="[515,678,1762,1786]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">
G. c. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Dejean" baseAuthorityYear="1831" box="[578,678,1762,1786]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Graphipterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cordiger">cordiger</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[740,946,1762,1786]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">G. c. subcordiger</emphasis>
and in the case of 
<emphasis box="[1179,1350,1762,1786]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">
G. c. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1848" box="[1242,1350,1762,1786]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Graphipterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hamatus">hamatus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">G. c. subhamatus</emphasis>
) or 
<taxonomicName box="[419,578,1794,1818]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Graphipterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wahlbergi">
<emphasis box="[419,578,1794,1818]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">G. wahlbergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(in the case of 
<emphasis box="[764,954,1794,1818]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">G. c. betshuana</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1016,1201,1794,1818]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Graphipterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="cordiger" subSpecies="wahlbergi">
<emphasis box="[1016,1201,1794,1818]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">G. c. wahlbergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). It is possible that even more taxa will be split from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Dejean" baseAuthorityYear="1831" box="[610,746,1826,1850]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Graphipterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cordiger">
<emphasis box="[610,746,1826,1850]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">G. cordiger</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[809,968,1826,1850]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Graphipterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wahlbergi">
<emphasis box="[809,968,1826,1850]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">G. wahlbergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
when additional material is available for study and the boundaries between the different geographic forms are studied in more detail.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[192,1440,194,314]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">
<taxonomicName box="[192,488,194,218]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Graphipterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wahlbergi">
<emphasis box="[192,488,194,218]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Graphipterus wahlbergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is generally distributed throughout the central and northern portions of the 
<collectingCountry box="[192,497,226,250]" name="South Africa" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Republic of South Africa</collectingCountry>
, where it can be locally abundant (
<bibRefCitation author="Basilewsky, P." box="[930,1186,226,250]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" pagination="1 - 472" refId="ref7374" refString="Basilewsky, P. 1977. Revision du genre Graphipterus Latreille (Coleoptera Carabidae). Musee Royal de l'Afrique Centrale, Annales, Serie in- 8 o, Sciences Zoologiques 221: 1 - 472." type="journal article" year="1977">Basilewsky 1977: 82</bibRefCitation>
). Populations of this species extend into adjacent portions of 
<collectingCountry box="[675,797,258,281]" name="Botswana" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Botswana</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[855,982,258,282]" name="Zimbabwe" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Zimbabwe</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Basilewsky, P." box="[996,1206,258,282]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" pagination="1 - 472" refId="ref7374" refString="Basilewsky, P. 1977. Revision du genre Graphipterus Latreille (Coleoptera Carabidae). Musee Royal de l'Afrique Centrale, Annales, Serie in- 8 o, Sciences Zoologiques 221: 1 - 472." type="journal article" year="1977">Basilewsky 1977</bibRefCitation>
: Carte 9). For a full synonymy for this species, see 
<bibRefCitation author="Basilewsky, P." box="[569,885,289,314]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" pagination="1 - 472" refId="ref7374" refString="Basilewsky, P. 1977. Revision du genre Graphipterus Latreille (Coleoptera Carabidae). Musee Royal de l'Afrique Centrale, Annales, Serie in- 8 o, Sciences Zoologiques 221: 1 - 472." type="journal article" year="1977">Basilewsky (1977: 76–77)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
